Package: ke
Title: Kinetic Ensemble for Nuclear Magnetic Resonance Structures
Version: 0.5
Authors@R: 
    person("Colin", "Smith", , "colin.smith@wesleyan.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4651-167X"))
Description: Tools for Kinetic Ensemble analysis of biomolecular
    structures using nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR) observables. Reads
    multistate coordinate ensembles and 'PDB' trajectories, detects
    equivalent proton permutations, constructs transition-rate and
    spectral-density data structures, and back-calculates dipole-dipole
    interaction tensors, cross-relaxation rates, and heteronuclear
    relaxation rates such as longitudinal (R1), transverse (R2), and
    nuclear Overhauser effect (NOE) data. Also provides utilities for
    preparing, reading, and writing restraint tables and for evaluating
    restraint energies from coordinates or trajectories. Methods are
    described in Smith et al. (2020) <doi:10.1007/s10858-019-00288-8> and
    Alhossary and Smith (2026) <doi:10.1021/acs.jpcb.5c08554>.
URL: https://github.com/smith-group/ke,
    https://smith-group.github.io/ke/
